<p>In a study of healthy young adults placed on a calorie-restricted diet designed to induce protein catabolism, MK-677 (25 mg daily for 7 days) significantly reversed the nitrogen-wasting effect. Peak GH response was 55.9 μg/L after the first dose (vs. ~9 μg/L placebo), and IGF-1 levels increased from diet-suppressed levels of 186 to 264 ng/mL. This study established MK-677's potential for muscle-sparing during caloric restriction — relevant for both clinical wasting conditions and dieting athletes.</p>

